Installation Guide (No Technical Knowledge Required)

PolyTrim can be installed in 3D Slicer in just a few minutes. No programming or Git experience is required.

Step 1 — Download PolyTrim

Go to the PolyTrim GitHub repository.

Click the green Code button.

Click Download ZIP.

Extract (unzip) the downloaded file to a location on your computer
(for example: C:\SlicerExtensions\PolyTrim).

⚠️ Important:
Inside the extracted folder, you should see:

PolyTrim.py

(and optionally PolyTrim.png).

Step 2 — Add PolyTrim to 3D Slicer

Open 3D Slicer.

Go to Edit → Application Settings.

Click on Modules.

Under Additional module paths, click Add.

Select the folder that contains PolyTrim.py.

Click OK.

Restart 3D Slicer.

Restarting is required.

Step 3 — Open the Module

After restarting:

Use the module search bar (top left).

Type:

PolyTrim

Open the module.

How to Use PolyTrim

Input folder
Select the folder containing your mesh files.

Input format
Choose either:

PLY

OBJ

Target polygons
Enter the desired polygon count
(e.g., 10000 or 20000).

Preserve topology
Recommended: keep this enabled.

Click Run.

Output

PolyTrim will automatically create a new folder inside your input directory:

input_folder/output/

The reduced meshes will be saved there in PLY format, with the target polygon count appended to the filename:

specimen_20000.ply
